# No Magic Strings

Do not compare, assign, or pass domain values as inline string literals.
Magic strings are an anti-pattern and make refactoring/error checking harder.

Use enums (or enum-like centralized declarations in `src/types/enums/`) and named members instead of raw strings.

## Required

- Replace inline domain strings like status, type, mode, role, and action names with enum members.
- Import and use shared enums from `src/types/enums/` (one model per file + barrel exports).
- Keep UI-only one-off labels as plain strings only when they are not domain identifiers.

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ Bad
if (secondProject.status === 'active') {
  // ...
}

// ✅ Good
if (secondProject.status === ProjectStatus.Active) {
  // ...
}
```

```typescript
// ❌ Bad
dispatch({ type: 'archive-project' })

// ✅ Good
dispatch({ type: ProjectAction.Archive })
```
